  "abstract": "The Office of the Comptroller of the Currency (OCC), the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System (Board), and the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation (FDIC) (Agencies) are proposing to amend their July 25, 1995, proposal to incorporate a measure for market risk into their respective risk-based capital standards. The proposed amendment would provide additional guidance to an institution about how the multiplication factor used to calculate capital requirements for market risk under the",
